- Oh, you're up?

250
00:10:19,994 --> 00:10:21,287
Are you here to work out?

251
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:22,955
- I already did.
- Where did you go?

252
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:24,999
- I just went for a light run. Yes.
- Oh, really?

253
00:10:25,791 --> 00:10:28,294
Park Kwang-chul,
you got this. You can do it this time.

254
00:10:28,377 --> 00:10:29,587
HEADS OUTSIDE
WHILE IMAGE TRAINING

255
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:32,590
30 MINUTES LATER

256
00:10:33,215 --> 00:10:35,051
RETURNING FROM A RUN

257
00:10:35,134 --> 00:10:36,886
You went on a run, huh?

258
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:39,430
Oh, man, geez, why are you up so early?

259
00:10:39,513 --> 00:10:40,806
This is when we usually wake up.

260
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:42,475
- Want some coffee?
- You drink coffee?

261
00:10:42,558 --> 00:10:44,977
- Yes. Can I please get one?
- Of course.

262
00:10:45,478 --> 00:10:48,022
- It's Ethiopian coffee. Sure.
- Thank you.

263
00:10:48,105 --> 00:10:50,483
- Everyone else is still asleep.
- They're all fast asleep.

264
00:10:50,566 --> 00:10:53,653
It couldn't have been easy
raising two daughters.

265
00:10:53,736 --> 00:10:55,821
- I got married young, so…
- Really?

266
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:58,449
I went into child-rearing blind.

267
00:10:58,532 --> 00:11:01,661
Some say that going into it blind
is definitely the better approach.

268
00:11:01,744 --> 00:11:03,162
Now that my kids are grown,

269
00:11:03,245 --> 00:11:04,997
- I have more time on my hands.
- Right, I get that.

270
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:06,666
- So, you got to raise them in advance?
- Yes.

271
00:11:06,749 --> 00:11:08,834
Which means you get to hang out
with your kids now.

272
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:10,503
- Yeah, exactly.
- You guys seem so close.

273
00:11:10,586 --> 00:11:11,629
I was jealous.

274
00:11:11,712 --> 00:11:13,756
Oh, there she is. Hello.

275
00:11:13,839 --> 00:11:15,966
- You're up early, Chae-won.
- Did you sleep well?

276
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:17,051
How'd you sleep?

277
00:11:17,134 --> 00:11:18,177
- Did you sleep well?
- Yes.

278
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:19,595
- Aren't you cold?
- No, I'm fine.

279
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:21,138
- You're good?
- Yes.

280
00:11:21,222 --> 00:11:22,848
How old did you say you were, Chae-won?

281
00:11:22,932 --> 00:11:24,350
- Fifth grade?
- No, eighth grade.

282
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:25,768
- Right.
- Oh, wow. Eighth grade.

283
00:11:25,851 --> 00:11:27,269
SURPRISED

284
00:11:27,353 --> 00:11:30,064
Oh. So you were born in 2011,
right, Chae-won?

285
00:11:30,147 --> 00:11:31,148
- Yes.
- Yes.

286
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:32,566
- Ji-ho was 2010.
- That's right.

287
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:35,569
I didn't notice it yesterday,
but you really take after your dad.

288
00:11:35,653 --> 00:11:37,279
- Your eyes--
- Oh, that's not good.

289
00:11:37,363 --> 00:11:39,657
- She hates it when people say that.
- Oh, really?

290
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:40,866
You look like your mom.

291
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:42,660
It can't be helped, Chae-won.

292
00:11:42,743 --> 00:11:44,537
You can't help
but look a bit like your dad.

293
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:46,122
Your mouth is shaped like his.

294
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:48,207
- Cute.
- We'll be on our way.

295
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:49,375
- Okay.
- See you later.

296
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:50,459
Right. Go on.

297
00:11:51,127 --> 00:11:52,878
It would be nice
to have a daughter like that.

298
00:11:52,962 --> 00:11:54,505
- You're a family man.
- God, I love it.

299
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:56,006
- Your kid's so grown up.
- It's nice.

300
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:59,093
- Then Ji-ho, he's…
- He's in ninth grade now.

301
00:11:59,176 --> 00:12:00,386
- Ninth grade?
- Uh-huh.

302
00:12:00,886 --> 00:12:02,221
He's a teenager.

303
00:12:02,304 --> 00:12:04,056
- You're right. He's all grown up.
- Ninth grade?

304
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:06,434
- Wow.
- It's scary how strong he is.

305
00:12:08,018 --> 00:12:09,311
You can do anything at that age.

306
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:13,482
His strength is growing, which is totally
different compared to my strength,

307
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:15,943
which is in free-fall. Man, he's just…

308
00:12:16,026 --> 00:12:17,361
- The energy.
- …he's unstoppable.

309
00:12:17,445 --> 00:12:20,030
- So much energy.
- Yep. I'm sorry you're in free fall.

310
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:22,241
Oh, hold on.

311
00:12:22,324 --> 00:12:24,410
- It's 6:46.
- Hey, I should get going.

312
00:12:24,493 --> 00:12:26,245
We have a wake-up mission, so get ready.

313
00:12:28,539 --> 00:12:31,500
Honey, when did you get
so many gray hairs? Come here.

314
00:12:32,793 --> 00:12:34,462
- They're noticeable today.
- Really?

315
00:12:34,545 --> 00:12:37,673
Back in <i>Hyo-ri's Bed & Breakfast</i>,
you didn't have a single gray.

316
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:39,884
Not a single one.

317
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:42,970
I imagine running a place like this…

318
00:12:43,971 --> 00:12:45,931
Dogs running around everywhere…

319
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:47,349
what do you think?

320
00:12:48,184 --> 00:12:49,935
You know what? Change of plans, honey.

321
00:12:50,019 --> 00:12:51,854
I'll go. You should stay tomorrow.

322
00:12:51,937 --> 00:12:54,315
- Okay, bye.
- You mean it?

323
00:12:54,398 --> 00:12:55,649
SHAKES HER HEAD

324
00:12:56,233 --> 00:12:57,234
By the way,

325
00:12:57,902 --> 00:12:59,779
when do they reveal their identities?

326
00:13:00,362 --> 00:13:01,906
Let's tell them to message us.

327
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:05,284
- I'm curious about a few.
- Pick a few people we're curious about.

328
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:07,912
The sun should be rising
right about now, right?

329
00:13:07,995 --> 00:13:09,121
Let's head outside, <i>oppa</i>.

330
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:10,956
The sun's rising.

331
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:12,833
Oh, I thought that was the sun.

332
00:13:12,917 --> 00:13:14,293
Seriously?

333
00:13:14,376 --> 00:13:16,837
- Let's go to the water.
- Wow.

334
00:13:17,421 --> 00:13:18,839
- It's a waterfall.
- A water park.

335
00:13:18,923 --> 00:13:21,008
Were we allowed to go over here?

336
00:13:21,383 --> 00:13:23,344
WITH LONG, BRISK STEPS

337
00:13:23,844 --> 00:13:25,304
THE FIRST TO CLIMB
ONTO THE WATERFALL

338
00:13:25,387 --> 00:13:28,349
- Wow, this is nice.
- I always want to climb on top of these.

339
00:13:28,432 --> 00:13:29,350
You wanna climb?

340
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:30,935
- Uh-huh.
- Oh.

341
00:13:31,018 --> 00:13:32,478
Look at the sky!

342
00:13:32,561 --> 00:13:34,438
- Oh, my. Wow.
- Gosh. It's so pretty.

343
00:13:34,522 --> 00:13:36,273
We should take a picture of that.

344
00:13:38,526 --> 00:13:41,362
- Wow, look at all the birds.
- Wow.

345
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:44,406
Jae-seok's balloon.

346
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:47,701
- Wish it was facing us.
- I know, right?

347
00:13:47,785 --> 00:13:49,245
The sky is so pretty right now.

348
00:13:49,328 --> 00:13:50,830
CAPTURING THE MORNING SCENERY

349
00:13:50,913 --> 00:13:53,958
- One, two, three.
- Three.

350
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:55,167
Whoosh.

351
00:13:56,794 --> 00:13:58,254
- Did you get it?
- Uh…

352
00:13:58,337 --> 00:13:59,463
You didn't get

353
00:13:59,547 --> 00:14:01,131
- the leaves properly. Again.
- Harder than it looks.

354
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:03,634
Two, three. Whoosh.

355
00:14:07,513 --> 00:14:09,265
No, what's with my face?

356
00:14:11,684 --> 00:14:13,727
WHILE THE MOUNTAIN COUPLE
IS OUT ON A WALK

357
00:14:15,145 --> 00:14:17,231
YEO-WON WAKES UP

358
00:14:18,148 --> 00:14:21,902
THE GUESTS WAKE UP ONE BY ONE

359
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:24,029
SWOOSH

360
00:14:24,113 --> 00:14:25,531
AN ANGELIC WAKE-UP

361
00:14:26,448 --> 00:14:29,785
RUSHING TO WASH UP

362
00:14:30,035 --> 00:14:30,870
WAKE-UP BROADCAST TIME

363
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:32,413
Okay, it's seven o'clock.

364
00:14:32,496 --> 00:14:33,998
- Excuse me, dear employees…
- Yes?

365
00:14:34,081 --> 00:14:35,457
Please switch that to a sun.

366
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:37,793
- Okay, got it. We'll switch it.
- Let's go.

367
00:14:44,091 --> 00:14:46,844
Uh, but where… where is everyone?

368
00:14:47,428 --> 00:14:48,512
PROCEEDING FOR NOW

369
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:51,265
Everyone, the morning has come.

370
00:14:51,765 --> 00:14:53,350
<i>…the morning has come.</i>

371
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:54,852
A VOICE ECHOES THROUGH THE B&B

372
00:14:54,935 --> 00:14:56,562
Did you all sleep well?

373
00:14:56,854 --> 00:14:58,355
EMPTY

374
00:14:58,439 --> 00:14:59,815
Everyone, the morning has come.

375
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:01,150
THE ONLY ONE WHO HASN'T WOKEN UP

376
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:02,860
Did you all sleep well?

377
00:15:02,943 --> 00:15:04,278
- Yeah.
- Uh-huh.

378
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:07,364
Since some people have gone for a shower,

379
00:15:07,448 --> 00:15:10,534
we'll give you the wake-up mission
once everyone has returned

380
00:15:10,618 --> 00:15:12,369
and is ready together.

381
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:14,580
- <i>…we'll give you the wake-up mission…</i>
- No way.

382
00:15:14,955 --> 00:15:16,749
A WAKE-UP MISSION?

383
00:15:16,832 --> 00:15:18,375
For each wake-up mission,

384
00:15:18,459 --> 00:15:22,838
we've prepared a surprise gift
that we're sure you'll enjoy.

385
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:25,758
Now, if everyone would please wake up,

386
00:15:25,841 --> 00:15:30,220
and join us for the second day
of <i>Jae-seok's B&B Rules!</i>

387
00:15:30,304 --> 00:15:32,431
Good morning. We'll see you in a bit.

388
00:15:32,514 --> 00:15:34,808
Once everyone's gathered,
there will be a wake-up mission.

389
00:15:34,892 --> 00:15:35,893
SEE YOU IN A BIT!

390
00:15:35,976 --> 00:15:38,187
This group really is different
from the last one.

391
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:39,271
Yeah, they're so different.

392
00:15:39,355 --> 00:15:42,274
Yeah, I mean Kwang-chul has already gone
for a run and everything.

393
00:15:42,983 --> 00:15:44,568
He's got so much energy.

394
00:15:44,652 --> 00:15:47,947
Oh, and Hyo-ri is already downstairs
doing her thing.

395
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:49,907
- Doing what?
- Cooking?

396
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:51,075
No, brewing coffee.

397
00:15:51,158 --> 00:15:52,701
Why are you acting so shocked?

398
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:54,286
It's not a soap opera.

399
00:15:54,370 --> 00:15:55,788
- "Cooking?"
- Sang-soon's back.

400
00:15:55,871 --> 00:15:57,581
- Ask him.
- <i>Hyung</i>, what were you doing?

401
00:15:57,665 --> 00:16:00,542
I was just making some coffee
and soaking the rice.

402
00:16:00,626 --> 00:16:02,461
Hey, Sang-soon makes great coffee
by the way.

403
00:16:02,544 --> 00:16:03,879
We already washed the rice.

404
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:05,756
MEANWHILE, IN THE LOBBY

405
00:16:06,298 --> 00:16:07,883
AS ONE WOULD EXPECT
OF THE B&B OG,

406
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:09,426
SHE NAILS THE SHOE ORGANIZATION

407
00:16:09,843 --> 00:16:10,844
Want some help?

408
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:13,681
No, no.
There was just too much stuff here.

409
00:16:16,058 --> 00:16:17,101
There we go.

410
00:16:19,895 --> 00:16:20,896
Did you sleep well?

411
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:22,898
- Good morning.
- Hello.

412
00:16:23,691 --> 00:16:25,484
MEANWHILE,
MIN-JU ALONE LIES IN BED

413
00:16:25,567 --> 00:16:26,610
Are you sick?

414
00:16:26,694 --> 00:16:28,320
Oh, hello.

415
00:16:28,904 --> 00:16:31,365
- I'm a bit-- I have a cold.
- A bit under the weather?

416
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:33,283
- Yeah.
- What should we do?

417
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:35,119
- Take anything?
- No, not yet.

418
00:16:35,202 --> 00:16:36,537
- Have any meds?
- Yeah.

419
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:38,163
I guess you overdid it yesterday.

420
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:40,082
Yeah, I've felt bad
since before I got here.

421
00:16:40,165 --> 00:16:41,291
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

422
00:16:43,127 --> 00:16:44,128
That's not good.

423
00:16:45,129 --> 00:16:46,714
Hyo-ri's already down there.

424
00:16:47,214 --> 00:16:48,882
I think everyone's here.

425
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:50,801
Sin-jeong, is your stomach okay?

426
00:16:50,884 --> 00:16:52,511
- Oh, yeah.
- Oh, that's a relief.

427
00:16:53,095 --> 00:16:54,471
STARTLED

428
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:56,598
- Oh, that's a relief.
- What's wrong?

429
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:57,683
WHAT'S GOING ON?

430
00:16:57,766 --> 00:16:59,852
It's a hornet.

431
00:16:59,935 --> 00:17:01,020
A hornet.

432
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:03,022
A hornet got in.

433
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:05,899
- A hornet?
- Yes, it's flying around here.

434
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:07,401
Just a second.

435
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:08,986
- Mr. Hornet.
- Can't let that happen.

436
00:17:09,570 --> 00:17:11,321
Time to bring back Mr. Hornet.

437
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:12,573
Where is it?

438
00:17:13,323 --> 00:17:14,867
- Over there. There.
- Over there.

439
00:17:14,950 --> 00:17:16,368
Oh. There it is.

440
00:17:16,452 --> 00:17:17,911
- It's over here.
- Where?

441
00:17:17,995 --> 00:17:19,163
It's coming back.

442
00:17:20,247 --> 00:17:21,248
Where is it?

443
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:24,668
It flew over there.

444
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:28,505
Get it. Hurry!

445
00:17:28,589 --> 00:17:30,549
It came back here, <i>oppa</i>. It came back.

446
00:17:31,884 --> 00:17:33,260
- It's there. In the center.
- Here. Here.

447
00:17:33,343 --> 00:17:35,971
- Wait, there, there! It's over there.
- Hold on, wait.

448
00:17:38,348 --> 00:17:40,267
- Hold on.
- Ah. Sh…

449
00:17:41,393 --> 00:17:43,353
- Over there. Woo-seok.
- Hold on.

450
00:17:43,437 --> 00:17:45,439
- Give me a second.
- Do it now.

451
00:17:45,522 --> 00:17:47,775
- Hit it.
- Run away. Hey!

452
00:17:47,858 --> 00:17:51,403
- Wait! Leave it! Leave it!
- Hey! Trap it, trap it!

453
00:17:51,487 --> 00:17:53,864
- Hey, it's getting away! Oh, no!
- No!

454
00:17:53,947 --> 00:17:55,115
VERY DISAPPOINTED

455
00:17:55,199 --> 00:17:57,409
- Did you get it?
- It went down there. Over there.

456
00:17:57,493 --> 00:17:59,286
- Oh, man…
- Oh, they got it.

457
00:17:59,369 --> 00:18:00,788
It got away!

458
00:18:00,871 --> 00:18:03,082
- It's here. All right.
- I hit it.

459
00:18:06,752 --> 00:18:08,337
- Nice!
- Kwang-chul got it!

460
00:18:09,463 --> 00:18:11,673
Yes! Come on.

461
00:18:12,257 --> 00:18:14,843
Okay, everyone, we have successfully dealt
with the hornet.

462
00:18:17,888 --> 00:18:20,474
He went back to announce that.

463
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:22,726
A MEMORY WORTH KEEPING

464
00:18:22,810 --> 00:18:24,311
As I mentioned earlier,

465
00:18:24,394 --> 00:18:28,107
in just a moment, we'll all be
partaking in a wake-up mission…

466
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:29,525
Ooh.

467
00:18:29,608 --> 00:18:31,151
…to start our day together.

468
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:32,945
- …to start our day together.
- What?

469
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:37,491
Everyone, for the wake-up mission,
I'll be playing a song for you.

470
00:18:37,574 --> 00:18:39,284
I'll be handing out a prize

471
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:42,454
to whoever manages to sing the song
from start to finish

472
00:18:42,538 --> 00:18:44,832
without making any mistakes.

473
00:18:45,499 --> 00:18:49,044
I love wake-up missions.
I've always wanted to try one.

474
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:53,382
It sounds so cool getting to try
something I've only seen on TV.

475
00:18:53,882 --> 00:18:56,426
Listen carefully.

476
00:18:56,510 --> 00:18:58,262
"YODEL OF THE FOREST"

477
00:18:58,345 --> 00:19:00,180
- We gotta listen.
- What?

478
00:19:01,431 --> 00:19:02,724
Here's the song.

479
00:19:02,808 --> 00:19:04,434
WE FOUND A MOUNTAIN VALLEY

480
00:19:04,518 --> 00:19:05,602
YOLOLADY YOLOLADY YOLAYWOODILY

481
00:19:05,686 --> 00:19:07,229
- What song is this?
- We have to sing this?

482
00:19:07,312 --> 00:19:08,313
WHERE A CLEAR STREAM FLOWS

483
00:19:08,397 --> 00:19:09,439
What is this?

484
00:19:09,523 --> 00:19:10,399
YOLOLADY YOLOLADY YOLAYWOODILY

485
00:19:10,482 --> 00:19:12,901
- We're never gonna get this.
- Let's go have fun, let's go…

486
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:14,153
WE HAD SO MUCH FUN LADY

487
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:18,115
SINGING A JOYFUL SONG
YOLOLAYWOODILY

488
00:19:18,198 --> 00:19:19,783
Wow, that's tough.

489
00:19:19,867 --> 00:19:21,577
Okay. So there it is.

490
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:24,580
Now, everyone,
let the wake-up mission commence.

491
00:19:24,663 --> 00:19:26,957
- "Hurry, yolaydily"?
- Yodelay.

492
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:28,375
- Singing a joyful song?
- What?

493
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:29,918
- "Had a lot of fun."
- Fun?

494
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:31,587
- Wait a sec.
- "We found a mountain valley."

495
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:33,297
We shouldn't be helping each other.

496
