- Good work, everyone.

732
00:27:47,207 --> 00:27:49,292
Thank you, Sang-soon. Thank you.

733
00:27:49,793 --> 00:27:51,836
YOGA CLASS IN THE GAME ROOM

734
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:56,591
FROM LEE HYO-RI TO…

735
00:27:56,675 --> 00:27:59,344
DIRECTOR ANANDA

736
00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:03,431
A SPECIAL CLASS TO CLEANSE
ONE'S TIRED BODY AND MIND

737
00:28:05,767 --> 00:28:09,688
DIRECTOR ANANDA'S YOGA CLASS

738
00:28:09,771 --> 00:28:11,314
<i>Unni</i>, do you do yoga?

739
00:28:11,398 --> 00:28:12,524
- Yeah.
- So are you coming?

740
00:28:12,607 --> 00:28:15,610
- You can fix your posture.
- We gotta get these straightened out.

741
00:28:15,694 --> 00:28:17,362
- You doing it?
- Uh-huh.

742
00:28:17,445 --> 00:28:18,613
YOGA CLASS IS OPTIONAL

743
00:28:19,698 --> 00:28:23,118
- Hello.
- Hello. Namaste.

744
00:28:23,201 --> 00:28:25,036
Namaste.

745
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:26,830
Please sit wherever you like.

746
00:28:26,913 --> 00:28:29,374
- Have you ever tried yoga?
- No.

747
00:28:29,457 --> 00:28:30,542
Yeah, same.

748
00:28:30,625 --> 00:28:33,169
I'm not flexible.
I can hear my joints pop.

749
00:28:33,253 --> 00:28:34,587
Now is your chance to learn.

750
00:28:35,213 --> 00:28:37,590
I was excited.
I'd always wanted to try it.

751
00:28:37,674 --> 00:28:40,760
I really wanted to take
a yoga class led by Hyo-ri.

752
00:28:40,844 --> 00:28:43,513
Everyone was excited,
so I had high expectations.

753
00:28:43,596 --> 00:28:44,472
HIGH HOPES

754
00:28:44,556 --> 00:28:45,557
FULLY BOOKED

755
00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:48,435
Everyone. Namaste.

756
00:28:48,518 --> 00:28:50,437
Namaste.

757
00:28:51,563 --> 00:28:53,690
Some people have fixed ideas about yoga.

758
00:28:53,773 --> 00:28:56,109
Like, "You can't do it
if you're not flexible."

759
00:28:56,192 --> 00:28:57,193
Yeah.

760
00:28:57,277 --> 00:29:00,530
But the truth is,
you do yoga because you're not flexible

761
00:29:00,613 --> 00:29:01,906
and you want to loosen up.

762
00:29:01,990 --> 00:29:06,619
Think of it as a way to loosen up your
joints and make your spine more flexible

763
00:29:06,703 --> 00:29:08,663
so you can feel better.

764
00:29:08,747 --> 00:29:10,623
We'll start with
some basic positions today.

765
00:29:10,707 --> 00:29:12,250
Stretch your legs out.

766
00:29:13,418 --> 00:29:15,128
Make sure your feet stay on the mat.

767
00:29:15,211 --> 00:29:18,173
Now slowly bend forward.

768
00:29:18,256 --> 00:29:20,091
Slowly bend forward.

769
00:29:20,967 --> 00:29:22,051
That's it.

770
00:29:23,261 --> 00:29:24,763
Slowly stretch

771
00:29:24,846 --> 00:29:26,890
- the tightened area behind the knee.
- I can't do it.

772
00:29:26,973 --> 00:29:30,143
Don't worry. Take your time and be gentle.

773
00:29:30,226 --> 00:29:31,394
MEANWHILE, AT THE GYMNASIUM

774
00:29:31,478 --> 00:29:32,479
Come on.

775
00:29:32,562 --> 00:29:35,982
When you're ready to head over, bring the
suggestion box to the dining area, please.

776
00:29:36,065 --> 00:29:37,275
Okay.

777
00:29:39,360 --> 00:29:41,029
How are there so many?

778
00:29:43,114 --> 00:29:44,282
This is insane.

779
00:29:44,365 --> 00:29:46,367
SHOCKING NUMBER OF SUGGESTIONS

780
00:29:48,077 --> 00:29:49,162
Ah, this is great.

781
00:29:50,830 --> 00:29:51,915
All right.

782
00:29:54,125 --> 00:29:55,418
<i>Urachacha!</i>

783
00:29:56,294 --> 00:29:57,712
<i>Urachacha!</i>

784
00:29:58,630 --> 00:29:59,964
What are you doing?

785
00:30:00,048 --> 00:30:01,382
<i>Urachacha!</i>

786
00:30:02,550 --> 00:30:04,093
HAS A FRONT-ROW SEAT

787
00:30:04,677 --> 00:30:06,513
MUST BE HIS WAY
OF PEPPING THEM UP

788
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:09,098
<i>"Urachacha"</i>? Really?

789
00:30:10,308 --> 00:30:12,310
Occupational hazard.

790
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:16,231
- Did you bring the box?
- Yes.

791
00:30:16,314 --> 00:30:17,774
There's a bunch of stuff in there.

792
00:30:17,857 --> 00:30:19,567
Kwang-soo has more.

793
00:30:19,651 --> 00:30:21,277
- For real?
- Yeah.

794
00:30:21,361 --> 00:30:23,071
- Let's see now.
- "Yu God."

795
00:30:23,154 --> 00:30:24,739
WHAT KIND OF SUGGESTIONS
COULD THERE BE?

796
00:30:24,823 --> 00:30:25,824
"Yu God."

797
00:30:25,907 --> 00:30:29,494
"Thanks to Yu God's punchy quips,
I had an absolute blast on the first day."

798
00:30:29,577 --> 00:30:32,330
"I was moved by the way you took
such gentle care of your guests."

799
00:30:33,498 --> 00:30:35,542
- Oh, it's a thank you letter.
- Oh. That's right.

800
00:30:35,625 --> 00:30:37,377
These aren't really suggestions.

801
00:30:37,460 --> 00:30:38,962
"I had indigestion today,

802
00:30:39,045 --> 00:30:41,714
so I'd like to express
my sincerest gratitude to the staff

803
00:30:41,798 --> 00:30:43,758
who took such good care of me."

804
00:30:43,842 --> 00:30:45,260
- "The food was so good."
- That's great.

805
00:30:45,343 --> 00:30:47,095
Did you hear that?

806
00:30:47,178 --> 00:30:49,013
SUPER PROUD

807
00:30:49,097 --> 00:30:50,515
Hey, Sang-soon, they love the food.

808
00:30:50,598 --> 00:30:51,933
- Really?
- They wrote that.

809
00:30:52,016 --> 00:30:55,061
- You should be so proud.
- Did they really? That's great.

810
00:30:56,437 --> 00:30:58,439
"Kwang-soo is too loud."

811
00:30:58,523 --> 00:31:00,358
Oh… Actually, I second that.

812
00:31:00,942 --> 00:31:04,153
Sorry, it's just that sometimes
your voice scares me, <i>hyung</i>.

813
00:31:04,237 --> 00:31:06,114
Is this for real?

814
00:31:06,197 --> 00:31:07,532
- Do you agree?
- Just tone it down.

815
00:31:07,615 --> 00:31:09,868
Sometimes it's a bit much.
You can go overboard.

816
00:31:11,661 --> 00:31:14,205
Tone it down a little, man.
Heed their advice.

817
00:31:14,289 --> 00:31:15,373
That suggestion's spot on.

818
00:31:15,456 --> 00:31:16,666
- Was it you?
- Huh?

819
00:31:16,749 --> 00:31:17,792
Was it you?

820
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:21,421
"Please stock some grain tea
for those who can't have caffeine."

821
00:31:21,504 --> 00:31:22,922
"Excellent ice cream."

822
00:31:23,006 --> 00:31:25,383
Hey, the convenience store just opened,

823
00:31:25,466 --> 00:31:28,177
so I'll go grab some grain tea
and Excellent real quick.

824
00:31:28,261 --> 00:31:29,262
Okay. Got it.

825
00:31:29,345 --> 00:31:31,556
- I'll be right back. Keep at it.
- Okay.

826
00:31:32,473 --> 00:31:38,021
OFF TO GRANT
THE GUESTS' REQUESTS

827
00:31:40,231 --> 00:31:41,274
Hello, sir.

828
00:31:42,025 --> 00:31:43,860
I'll be taking a little bit of each.

829
00:31:44,360 --> 00:31:46,237
Okay, Solomon's Seal.

830
00:31:46,321 --> 00:31:48,531
I'll be clearing out
your shelves today, sir.

831
00:31:48,615 --> 00:31:49,782
I need all of this.

832
00:31:50,533 --> 00:31:52,368
I'll just buy one of everything.

833
00:31:52,452 --> 00:31:53,870
And the Excellent.

834
00:31:56,289 --> 00:31:57,999
That should do it.

835
00:31:58,082 --> 00:31:59,542
Oh, my goodness.

836
00:31:59,626 --> 00:32:01,336
VERY SATISFIED

837
00:32:01,419 --> 00:32:03,963
- Want me to make you a cup of coffee?
- Yes, <i>hyung</i>.

838
00:32:04,047 --> 00:32:06,090
- No problem.
- Thank you, <i>hyung</i>.

839
00:32:06,883 --> 00:32:08,468
- Americano?
- Yes, please.

840
00:32:10,345 --> 00:32:11,763
Smells amazing.

841
00:32:12,305 --> 00:32:13,681
Wow.

842
00:32:13,765 --> 00:32:15,975
Waking up in the morning
having this smell…

843
00:32:16,059 --> 00:32:18,937
- Nothing better than waking up with this.
- Totally. That feels amazing.

844
00:32:19,020 --> 00:32:20,897
I want the scent to linger in my home.

845
00:32:22,190 --> 00:32:23,399
Does your home smell?

846
00:32:23,483 --> 00:32:24,484
INNOCENTLY MALICIOUS

847
00:32:24,567 --> 00:32:25,902
No, it doesn't smell.

848
00:32:26,527 --> 00:32:28,571
This is Ethiopian Chelbesa.

849
00:32:29,489 --> 00:32:30,490
- There you are.
- Thank you.

850
00:32:30,573 --> 00:32:31,532
Thank you.

851
00:32:32,867 --> 00:32:33,952
Mmm…

852
00:32:37,872 --> 00:32:38,915
Mmm…

853
00:32:38,998 --> 00:32:40,416
Ah…

854
00:32:42,043 --> 00:32:43,962
- Do you like this kind?
- It's lovely.

855
00:32:44,045 --> 00:32:45,380
- You like it?
- Yeah.

856
00:32:45,463 --> 00:32:47,090
IT'S THE LITTLE JOYS…

857
00:32:47,173 --> 00:32:49,133
It's got a little bit of acidity.

858
00:32:49,634 --> 00:32:51,636
God, this is so good.

859
00:32:51,719 --> 00:32:53,346
It's got this somewhat floral,

860
00:32:53,429 --> 00:32:55,932
- tea-like… tea-like scent.
- It is like tea, yeah.

861
00:32:56,015 --> 00:32:58,226
So we can have this, and then we eat.

862
00:32:58,309 --> 00:33:00,979
Oh, shoot.
We should stop steaming these now.

863
00:33:01,062 --> 00:33:02,730
TIME FOR BREAKFAST

864
00:33:02,814 --> 00:33:04,065
Oh, man.

865
00:33:04,148 --> 00:33:05,858
THOUGH IT WAS SHORT-LIVED,
WE WERE HAPPY…

866
00:33:05,942 --> 00:33:07,860
This is such a nice way
to spend the morning.

867
00:33:07,944 --> 00:33:09,487
Wow, you made some eggs?

868
00:33:09,570 --> 00:33:11,114
This is specifically for making eggs?

869
00:33:11,197 --> 00:33:12,907
Yeah. I steamed them.

870
00:33:12,991 --> 00:33:14,075
We need to peel some fruit.

871
00:33:14,158 --> 00:33:16,786
- Apples, persimmons, and tangerines.
- Tangerines.

872
00:33:16,869 --> 00:33:19,372
PREPARING FRUIT FOR THE SALAD

873
00:33:21,124 --> 00:33:22,875
Woo-seok, something's bugging me.

874
00:33:23,418 --> 00:33:24,585
Where's Ye-eun?

875
00:33:25,670 --> 00:33:27,380
RIGHT… YE-EUN'S MISSING…

876
00:33:27,964 --> 00:33:30,299
- I mean, I'm not trying to be nosy, but…
- Mm-hmm.

877
00:33:30,383 --> 00:33:32,468
…I'm just dying to know
where she is right now.

878
00:33:32,552 --> 00:33:34,679
- Where is she?
- Maybe she's doing yoga.

879
00:33:34,762 --> 00:33:35,847
Do you think?

880
00:33:36,347 --> 00:33:38,933
Let's bend down. You're all doing great.

881
00:33:39,017 --> 00:33:41,436
What's up, Ye-eun?

882
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:44,313
- You can't bend any further?
- No.

883
00:33:44,981 --> 00:33:46,149
Why don't you try?

884
00:33:47,483 --> 00:33:48,484
A little more.

885
00:33:50,069 --> 00:33:51,988
A little more, and relax your core.

886
00:33:52,655 --> 00:33:55,116
- A little more.
- Ow. That hurts.

887
00:33:56,242 --> 00:33:59,370
Try to breathe comfortably
without frowning.

888
00:33:59,454 --> 00:34:02,165
Now for the next position,
let's lie down on our stomachs.

889
00:34:02,248 --> 00:34:04,250
The cobra pose, <i>Bhujjangasana</i>.

890
00:34:04,333 --> 00:34:07,295
Both hands under your shoulders,
spread your fingers wide,

891
00:34:07,378 --> 00:34:10,173
and slowly lift just your upper body.
That's it.

892
00:34:10,256 --> 00:34:14,469
Look, we're gonna stretch our backs,
hands on the mat, fingers spread wide.

893
00:34:15,094 --> 00:34:16,095
You're good at this.

894
00:34:16,179 --> 00:34:18,973
No wonder you're so good
at doing sexy dance moves.

895
00:34:19,057 --> 00:34:20,224
<i>…Yodelay, yodelayhihi </i>

896
00:34:20,308 --> 00:34:23,269
Oh, doing great. You're doing great.
Chae-eun, breathe.

897
00:34:23,352 --> 00:34:25,396
Try bending your knees.

898
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:28,399
Extend your feet towards your head.

899
00:34:28,483 --> 00:34:30,193
This is the final pose, everyone.

900
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:32,945
NO WAY

901
00:34:33,029 --> 00:34:34,572
She's so flexible.

902
00:34:34,655 --> 00:34:36,657
Chae-eun here should do yoga.

903
00:34:36,741 --> 00:34:41,079
This pose is called <i>Rajakapotasana</i>,
and even seasoned yogis struggle with it.

904
00:34:41,162 --> 00:34:42,997
- Wow.
- Nice.

905
00:34:43,081 --> 00:34:44,957
THIS POSE IS SO DIFFICULT THAT…

906
00:34:45,041 --> 00:34:46,959
THIS IS HOW FAR
THE AVERAGE PERSON GETS

907
00:34:47,043 --> 00:34:48,795
- Are you there, I-an?
- Huh?

908
00:34:48,878 --> 00:34:51,130
- Are you there yet?
- I'm nowhere near there.

909
00:34:51,214 --> 00:34:52,799
I can't do it. This is so hard.

910
00:34:53,382 --> 00:34:55,259
- Four. That's it.
- I can't do it.

911
00:34:55,343 --> 00:34:57,261
Five. Just a little more.

912
00:34:57,345 --> 00:35:00,223
Now kick your legs all the way over
till they're behind your head.

913
00:35:00,306 --> 00:35:01,599
This is the final pose.

914
00:35:01,682 --> 00:35:02,892
HALASANA PLOUGH POSE

915
00:35:02,975 --> 00:35:06,187
Beginners can lower their legs,
and use that momentum.

916
00:35:07,271 --> 00:35:08,564
Oh, God.

917
00:35:09,148 --> 00:35:10,358
Ow!

918
00:35:10,441 --> 00:35:13,486
That's it! Now let's do the bridge
like you see in <i>The Exorcist.</i>

919
00:35:14,070 --> 00:35:16,030
Let's all try that just once.

920
00:35:16,114 --> 00:35:18,950
That's the best stretch there is,
wouldn't you all agree?

921
00:35:19,575 --> 00:35:23,121
Okay, bend your legs
and bring your feet up to your butt.

922
00:35:23,204 --> 00:35:25,706
- Bend your knees…
- Then grab your ankles,

923
00:35:25,790 --> 00:35:27,333
then lift up your pelvis high.

924
00:35:27,416 --> 00:35:28,876
That's it. Push it up higher.

925
00:35:28,960 --> 00:35:30,920
Oh! You're already there!

926
00:35:31,003 --> 00:35:32,588
Chae-eun's a yoga prodigy.

927
00:35:32,672 --> 00:35:34,173
Wow. How do you even…

928
00:35:34,257 --> 00:35:35,716
Keep pushing, and plant

929
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:37,760
- the top of your head on the floor.
- Oh, God!

930
00:35:37,844 --> 00:35:39,595
Heave ho! That's it.

931
00:35:39,679 --> 00:35:41,430
I used to be able to do this.

932
00:35:42,014 --> 00:35:44,058
But I can't anymore.

933
00:35:44,142 --> 00:35:46,144
Ye-eun. Three.

934
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:48,980
Five.

935
00:35:49,063 --> 00:35:51,023
Push, push. Six.

936
00:35:51,107 --> 00:35:53,109
Push, push. Six.

937
00:35:53,192 --> 00:35:55,319
See? You can do it. Now seven.

938
00:35:55,403 --> 00:35:57,238
THE SOUND OF BECOMING HEALTHIER

939
00:35:57,321 --> 00:35:58,489
Eight. Push up.

940
00:35:58,573 --> 00:36:00,449
K.O.

941
00:36:00,533 --> 00:36:03,119
Pull your chin in
as you return to the beginning.

942
00:36:03,202 --> 00:36:04,787
Well done. Well done.

943
00:36:05,371 --> 00:36:09,250
Okay, this is where it usually ends,
but who here wants to try a headstand?

944
00:36:09,333 --> 00:36:12,336
- Who wants to try practicing a headstand?
- Me.

945
00:36:12,420 --> 00:36:14,255
Beginners can get injured doing this pose.

946
00:36:14,338 --> 00:36:16,465
Only try it if you know how to fall.

947
00:36:16,549 --> 00:36:19,135
We'll give it a try, but be careful.

948
00:36:19,218 --> 00:36:22,054
First, sit at the end of the mat.

949
00:36:22,638 --> 00:36:24,432
Then grab your arms so that your hands

950
00:36:24,515 --> 00:36:26,809
are equal distances apart
from your elbows, like this.

951
00:36:26,893 --> 00:36:28,853
Grab your elbows
and place them on the floor.

952
00:36:29,854 --> 00:36:33,191
Next, fix your elbows in place
and interlock your fingers.

953
00:36:33,733 --> 00:36:36,152
Then plant the top of your head
on the floor and hold it.

954
00:36:36,235 --> 00:36:37,778
Hold it tight with your hands.

955
00:36:37,862 --> 00:36:39,780
Next, straighten out your legs.

956
00:36:40,615 --> 00:36:43,910
After that, walk over as far as you can.

957
00:36:43,993 --> 00:36:47,788
Next, lift your legs one by one like this.

958
00:36:48,581 --> 00:36:50,249
Then straighten your knees.

959
00:36:52,251 --> 00:36:54,420
Next, extend your legs.

960
00:36:54,503 --> 00:36:55,796
Whoa.

961
00:36:56,631 --> 00:36:58,841
- How is that even possible?
- That's skill.

962
00:36:58,925 --> 00:37:01,135
- Holy crap, she's actually doing it.
- Wow.

963
00:37:01,802 --> 00:37:03,429
Okay, who pulled it off?

964
00:37:03,512 --> 00:37:04,513
That's it!

965
00:37:05,264 --> 00:37:07,433
Then, straighten your knees.
Next, extend your legs.

966
00:37:07,516 --> 00:37:09,185
YOUNG-GWANG FOLLOWED
THE INSTRUCTIONS TO A T

967
00:37:09,268 --> 00:37:11,062
Okay, who else wants to try?

968
00:37:11,771 --> 00:37:13,773
It's soft, so you won't get hurt.

969
00:37:14,690 --> 00:37:16,400
See that? He didn't listen.

970
00:37:16,484 --> 00:37:18,277
I said the edge of the mat, right?

971
00:37:20,196 --> 00:37:22,615
If he fell here, it might hurt.

972
00:37:24,033 --> 00:37:25,534
Oh, but still, you did good.

973
00:37:25,618 --> 00:37:26,827
That's it.

974
00:37:28,329 --> 00:37:29,956
Lie down now. Lie down.

975
00:37:30,665 --> 00:37:31,791
Lie down.

976
00:37:31,874 --> 00:37:33,251
Rest for a bit.

977
00:37:33,751 --> 00:37:34,961
Rest.

978
00:37:35,586 --> 00:37:39,215
This final pose where you lie down
is called <i>Shavasana</i>,

979
00:37:39,298 --> 00:37:41,300
which means "corpse pose."

980
00:37:41,384 --> 00:37:45,304
Relax every single part of your body
one by one by one.

981
00:37:45,388 --> 00:37:51,060
Everyone, we did all those previous poses
to reach this final relaxation pose.

982
00:37:51,978 --> 00:37:55,564
Doing that pose
helped us keep nice and relaxed.

983
00:37:55,648 --> 00:37:59,735
I guess I was somewhat biased against it
because I thought it was just stretching.

984
00:37:59,819 --> 00:38:01,946
But as I kept holding the poses
and focusing,

985
00:38:02,029 --> 00:38:05,199
I realized that it was offering
a decent workout.

986
00:38:05,283 --> 00:38:08,828
It let me take the time
to solely focus on myself.

987
00:38:08,911 --> 00:38:11,414
It was nice to stretch after so long.

988
00:38:11,914 --> 00:38:15,001
Thank you for your hard work
so early in the morning.

989
00:38:15,084 --> 00:38:17,086
- Namaste. Thank you.
- Namaste.

990
00:38:17,169 --> 00:38:20,381
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

991
00:38:22,174 --> 00:38:24,885
TOTALLY WIPED OUT

992
00:38:24,969 --> 00:38:27,888
Okay, as for the mats,
gather them and put them over there.

993
00:38:27,972 --> 00:38:29,181
I feel so clear-headed.

994
00:38:29,265 --> 00:38:31,559
- Yeah, I feel like I can see clearly.
- Mm-hmm.

995
00:38:31,642 --> 00:38:33,477
Yeah. Man, that was refreshing.

996
00:38:33,561 --> 00:38:34,603
I feel great.

997
00:38:34,687 --> 00:38:37,273
I mean, we even did yoga,
but it's still early.

998
00:38:38,024 --> 00:38:40,318
Are we going to have breakfast right away?

999
00:38:40,401 --> 00:38:42,778
NOT YET…

1000
00:38:43,446 --> 00:38:45,364
HYO-RI RETURNS

1001
00:38:45,448 --> 00:38:46,699
How's it going?

1002
00:38:47,199 --> 00:38:48,200
Thanks for everything.

1003
00:38:48,284 --> 00:38:49,952
- Namaste.
- Did it go well?

1004
00:38:50,036 --> 00:38:52,330
<i>Shanti, shanti, shanti, shanti.</i>

1005
00:38:52,413 --> 00:38:54,665
- Namaste.
- Your face is really glowing right now.

1006
00:38:54,749 --> 00:38:56,709
- Oh, really?
- Is that the yoga?

1007
00:38:56,792 --> 00:38:59,086
- Yeah? I only led it.
- Really?

1008
00:38:59,170 --> 00:39:01,339
- I really think everyone liked it.
- Ye-eun.

1009
00:39:01,422 --> 00:39:03,841
Oh, Ye-eun's face is also really…
Wow, she looks so--

1010
00:39:03,924 --> 00:39:05,468
Ye-eun didn't do any yoga.

1011
00:39:05,551 --> 00:39:07,553
She just was spread out like this
the whole time.

1012
00:39:07,636 --> 00:39:09,263
- Wait, she didn't do yoga?
- No.

1013
00:39:09,930 --> 00:39:11,140
Stretching.

1014
00:39:11,223 --> 00:39:12,308
Ye-eun needed it though.

1015
00:39:12,391 --> 00:39:14,101
- Right.
- I'm glad she took the time.

1016
00:39:14,185 --> 00:39:17,355
- She needs to take care of her health.
- Yes, I really needed that.

1017
00:39:17,438 --> 00:39:18,439
A BODY THAT NEEDS CARE

1018
00:39:18,522 --> 00:39:20,691
Honey, this is hard to blend.

1019
00:39:20,775 --> 00:39:22,693
You need to add way more water.

1020
00:39:22,777 --> 00:39:24,820
Give it to me. I'll do it.

1021
00:39:27,990 --> 00:39:29,784
JAE-SEOK ARRIVES JUST IN TIME

1022
00:39:29,867 --> 00:39:31,827
Oh, looks like Jae-seok's back.

1023
00:39:34,747 --> 00:39:36,582
- Welcome back.
- There he is.

1024
00:39:36,665 --> 00:39:38,209
- Thanks for picking those up.
- Thank you.

1025
00:39:38,292 --> 00:39:39,919
Oh, please. It was nothing.

1026
00:39:40,711 --> 00:39:42,505
The grain and barley tea.

1027
00:39:43,714 --> 00:39:44,965
BUSY UPON ARRIVAL

1028
00:39:45,049 --> 00:39:48,719
I brought some loose-leaf barley tea and
bags for those who can't have caffeine.

1029
00:39:48,803 --> 00:39:50,721
I got a bunch of different drinks.

1030
00:39:50,805 --> 00:39:52,056
Should I start organizing them?

1031
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:54,433
Someone said they wanted some Excellent.

1032
00:39:54,517 --> 00:39:55,976
- Oh, that was me.
- Huh?

1033
00:39:56,060 --> 00:39:57,728
These used to slap when I was a kid.

1034
00:39:57,812 --> 00:40:00,648
- They only had one left. Enjoy.
- Thank you.

1035
00:40:00,731 --> 00:40:03,609
They need to go
in the other cabinet. Lots of choices now.

1036
00:40:03,692 --> 00:40:05,444
- It's a lot more diverse now.
- Uh-huh.

1037
00:40:08,697 --> 00:40:11,784
NEW ITEMS IN STOCK
AT THE SNACK BAR

1038
00:40:12,910 --> 00:40:14,995
The snack bar
should be all stocked up now.

1039
00:40:15,079 --> 00:40:16,997
Wow, oh, there's coffee.

1040
00:40:17,081 --> 00:40:18,290
Thank you.

1041
00:40:18,374 --> 00:40:20,084
There's a bunch of new stuff to try out.

1042
00:40:20,167 --> 00:40:21,669
- Right. Thank you.
- Thank you.

1043
00:40:21,752 --> 00:40:24,130
Where is the bottle of Jetty?

1044
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:28,217
- I like these.
- You have those every day.

1045
00:40:28,300 --> 00:40:29,802
THE SNACK BAR
IS POPULAR AS ALWAYS

1046
00:40:30,553 --> 00:40:32,555
We should get started on the toast,

1047
00:40:32,638 --> 00:40:34,265
don't you think? Hold on.

1048
00:40:34,348 --> 00:40:36,392
Whose team was in charge
of breakfast again?

1049
00:40:36,475 --> 00:40:38,144
- Breakfast?
- Our team.

1050
00:40:38,227 --> 00:40:40,146
I'll call over Team Ye-eun.

1051
00:40:40,229 --> 00:40:41,397
No, it's Team Woo-seok.

1052
00:40:41,480 --> 00:40:42,565
No, it's Team Woo-seok.

1053
00:40:42,648 --> 00:40:44,859
- Oh, Woo-seok.
- Yeah.

1054
00:40:45,651 --> 00:40:48,320
Sorry to interrupt, but can you please
go tell Team Woo-seok

1055
00:40:48,404 --> 00:40:49,905
to come over
and start preparing breakfast?

1056
00:40:49,989 --> 00:40:50,990
- Okay.
- Sure.

1057
00:40:51,866 --> 00:40:53,701
FIND TEAM WOO-SEOK

1058
00:40:53,784 --> 00:40:55,077
Ye-rin.

1059
00:40:55,744 --> 00:40:57,496
They need help making breakfast.

1060
00:40:57,580 --> 00:40:58,831
They asked for you.

1061
00:40:59,331 --> 00:41:01,083
They said you should come help
with breakfast.

1062
00:41:01,167 --> 00:41:02,543
Oh, that's right.

1063
00:41:03,169 --> 00:41:05,296
- They're calling Team Woo-seok.
- Breakfast.

1064
00:41:06,046 --> 00:41:07,089
Come on, Dad!

1065
00:41:07,173 --> 00:41:09,383
- They want me to help too?
- Right.

1066
00:41:09,467 --> 00:41:10,634
- Team Woo-seok?
- Yes.

1067
00:41:10,718 --> 00:41:13,220
Team Woo-seok,
you have to prepare breakfast with us.

1068
00:41:13,304 --> 00:41:14,889
- Okay.
- Got it.

1069
00:41:14,972 --> 00:41:17,725
This isn't a punishment
since we get to do it all together.

1070
00:41:19,143 --> 00:41:20,895
It's awesome.

1071
00:41:20,978 --> 00:41:24,273
Man. Kwang-chul, you're so positive
all the time.

1072
00:41:24,356 --> 00:41:26,066
This is going to be a good breakfast.

1073
00:41:27,318 --> 00:41:29,612
What will we do when the pros leave?

1074
00:41:29,695 --> 00:41:31,030
I've decided to leave him behind.

1075
00:41:31,113 --> 00:41:32,781
- Oh, really? Wow.
- Uh-huh.

1076
00:41:32,865 --> 00:41:34,575
Oh, no, no.

1077
00:41:34,658 --> 00:41:37,286
You mean it? We'd be so grateful.

1078
00:41:37,369 --> 00:41:40,164
- I'd be trapped here.
- Just hitch a ride with Woo-seok.

1079
00:41:40,247 --> 00:41:41,999
Totally. You can ride with me.

1080
00:41:42,082 --> 00:41:44,793
- Ah, that's perfect.
- Stop.

1081
00:41:44,877 --> 00:41:46,629
- Sang-soon…
- Oh, God.

1082
00:41:46,712 --> 00:41:49,215
Sang-soon, get comfy.

1083
00:41:52,510 --> 00:41:54,011
Oh, this early?

1084
00:41:54,803 --> 00:41:55,971
She's already working at it.

1085
00:41:56,055 --> 00:41:57,223
Who's working at what?

1086
00:41:57,306 --> 00:41:58,474
Working out.

1087
00:41:58,557 --> 00:42:04,396
One, two, three, four, five.

1088
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:05,689
Breathe in, breathe out.

1089
00:42:06,315 --> 00:42:08,317
Look at her forearm muscles.

1090
00:42:08,400 --> 00:42:10,361
It looks so effortless.

1091
00:42:11,737 --> 00:42:12,863
How was it?

1092
00:42:12,947 --> 00:42:15,741
- God. Felt great. Sick.
- Feel those gains.

1093
00:42:16,325 --> 00:42:18,327
They're all really good at working out.

1094
00:42:18,994 --> 00:42:21,080
- Are they athletes?
- I think so.

1095
00:42:21,163 --> 00:42:23,040
It definitely seems like they are.

1096
00:42:23,832 --> 00:42:26,794
I'm telling you, they're all
pro athletes. Just look at them.

1097
00:42:26,877 --> 00:42:28,629
Relax. Relax your traps.

1098
00:42:28,712 --> 00:42:30,005
Two…

1099
00:42:30,089 --> 00:42:31,590
- You're lifting your left heel.
- …three.

1100
00:42:31,674 --> 00:42:33,509
- Move your right foot back.
- Back?

1101
00:42:34,134 --> 00:42:36,095
TEAM FRENCH TOAST

1102
00:42:36,178 --> 00:42:38,514
They taste better
when you really soak them.

1103
00:42:39,181 --> 00:42:41,100
EFFORTLESS EXECUTION
BY THE FRENCH TOAST VETERAN

1104
00:42:41,183 --> 00:42:43,811
- The toast looks amazing.
- Doesn't it?

1105
00:42:43,894 --> 00:42:47,648
- Man, they're perfectly cooked right now.
- That looks so good.

1106
00:42:47,731 --> 00:42:49,066
- It's the prefect color.
- Totally.

1107
00:42:49,149 --> 00:42:51,026
Let's sprinkle on some sugar.

1108
00:42:51,110 --> 00:42:53,445
- You've done this, Chae-eun?
- Yes, at home.

1109
00:42:53,529 --> 00:42:56,198
- How old are you?
- Don't tell them.

1110
00:42:56,282 --> 00:42:57,992
- That's not allowed?
- No.

1111
00:42:58,075 --> 00:43:00,035
Second or third year of high school?

1112
00:43:00,119 --> 00:43:02,246
- I don't look younger?
- No, you don't.

1113
00:43:02,329 --> 00:43:04,707
- Yeah, I'm getting more high school.
- Oh, really?

1114
00:43:04,790 --> 00:43:06,875
You and your older sister must be
close, Chae-eun.

1115
00:43:06,959 --> 00:43:09,420
Yep. She listens to me most, I would say.

1116
00:43:09,503 --> 00:43:10,713
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

1117
00:43:10,796 --> 00:43:13,716
Because she's scarier than my dad.

1118
00:43:13,799 --> 00:43:14,925
I think that's normal.

1119
00:43:15,634 --> 00:43:17,177
Younger siblings always fear

1120
00:43:17,261 --> 00:43:19,221
- the older sibling the most.
- Mmm.

1121
00:43:20,848 --> 00:43:24,101
WOO-SEOK DILIGENTLY
READIES THE INGREDIENTS

1122
00:43:26,312 --> 00:43:27,479
FOLLOWING SANG-SOON'S RECIPE

1123
00:43:27,563 --> 00:43:29,398
Mayonnaise, mustard.

1124
00:43:29,481 --> 00:43:30,816
Wow, that looks delicious.

1125
00:43:31,317 --> 00:43:33,527
- Looks good, right?
- It looks so good.

1126
00:43:36,530 --> 00:43:40,534
HYO-RI BRIEFLY HEADS TO THE
SNACK BAR TO QUENCH HER THIRST

1127
00:43:41,118 --> 00:43:44,079
- What time are you leaving?
- We'll be leaving after lunch.

1128
00:43:44,622 --> 00:43:47,124
And if you haven't told me anything
before that,

1129
00:43:47,207 --> 00:43:50,127
I'll just have to remember you
as the person you were.

1130
00:43:50,210 --> 00:43:52,838
I'll leave without knowing
your profession, your age,

1131
00:43:52,921 --> 00:43:54,423
or whether you're younger than me.

1132
00:43:55,049 --> 00:43:57,593
Are you married, Nam-jin?
I couldn't help but notice

1133
00:43:57,676 --> 00:44:00,095
- you're wearing a wedding ring.
- I am married.

1134
00:44:00,638 --> 00:44:03,349
- You look like so young though.
- I am young.

1135
00:44:04,016 --> 00:44:05,684
I got married before my 30s.

1136
00:44:05,768 --> 00:44:07,394
Oh. You married early.

1137
00:44:07,478 --> 00:44:08,646
Is your older brother married?

1138
00:44:09,563 --> 00:44:11,482
- So you got married before him, huh?
- Yep.

1139
00:44:11,565 --> 00:44:13,025
THE OLDER BROTHER IS UNMARRIED

1140
00:44:13,108 --> 00:44:15,319
- These things happen.
- Aren't you gonna get married?

1141
00:44:16,111 --> 00:44:17,863
Oh, you don't want to get married?

1142
00:44:17,946 --> 00:44:20,240
- No. No.
- So you haven't found a partner yet?

1143
00:44:20,324 --> 00:44:21,742
Try going on <i>I'm SOLO.</i>

1144
00:44:21,825 --> 00:44:23,243
HIGHLY RECOMMEND
APPEARING ON <i>I'M SOLO</i>

1145
00:44:23,327 --> 00:44:25,120
<i>I'm SOLO </i>is my favorite show.

1146
00:44:25,204 --> 00:44:26,413
- It's good.
- I know, right?

1147
00:44:26,497 --> 00:44:27,706
Did you see the recent season?

1148
00:44:27,790 --> 00:44:29,333
- It was crazy.
- It was insane.

1149
00:44:29,416 --> 00:44:31,710
- So entertaining.
- So much fun.

1150
00:44:31,794 --> 00:44:33,420
I wait and watch it with <i>oppa</i>.

1151
00:44:33,504 --> 00:44:34,838
- I see.
- Neither one of us is allowed

1152
00:44:34,922 --> 00:44:36,340
to watch it without the other.

1153
00:44:36,423 --> 00:44:38,175
I don't watch <i>I'm SOLO</i>, so…

1154
00:44:38,258 --> 00:44:39,468
- Oh, you don't?
- No, I don't.

1155
00:44:39,551 --> 00:44:41,095
You should watch it. It's super fun.

1156
00:44:41,178 --> 00:44:43,555
- Oh, when it comes to TV…
- You don't watch much TV?

1157
00:44:43,639 --> 00:44:45,599
- No, I don't watch much.
- And usually when I watch,

1158
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:47,184
I scream at the TV.

1159
00:44:47,267 --> 00:44:49,978
- "Quiet down! You're so loud!"
- And he keeps asking me what I'm doing.

1160
00:44:50,062 --> 00:44:52,690
You two have very different personalities.

1161
00:44:52,773 --> 00:44:54,108
- Yes.
- Even your hairstyles

1162
00:44:54,191 --> 00:44:57,486
- and the way you dress are different.
- His wife really liked it

1163
00:44:57,569 --> 00:45:00,114
- when his hair was grown out.
- Oh, she likes it long?

1164
00:45:00,197 --> 00:45:02,324
Which is why he has it so long right now.

1165
00:45:02,825 --> 00:45:06,620
I need you to know, my wife looked up
to you so much, Hyo-ri.

1166
00:45:07,204 --> 00:45:10,499
I'm not someone worth looking up to,
so this is embarrassing.

1167
00:45:10,582 --> 00:45:11,750
Don't say that.

1168
00:45:12,668 --> 00:45:15,963
We also did volunteer work
at animal shelters.

1169
00:45:16,046 --> 00:45:18,298
- Oh, you volunteer? Really?
- My wife and I.

1170
00:45:18,382 --> 00:45:19,883
- Yes. We also fostered dogs…
- Really?

1171
00:45:19,967 --> 00:45:22,553
- …and sent them to Canada for adoption.
- No way, really?

1172
00:45:22,636 --> 00:45:24,304
So do you still volunteer?

1173
00:45:24,805 --> 00:45:27,433
Well… I…

1174
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:30,853
What, did you stop?

1175
00:45:32,980 --> 00:45:35,357
Unfortunately, she passed away.

1176
00:45:35,858 --> 00:45:37,901
- Huh?
- She passed away.

1177
00:45:39,403 --> 00:45:41,864
- Oh, really?
- Yes, she passed away.

1178
00:45:41,947 --> 00:45:44,783
It was last year.
In September of last year.

1179
00:45:44,867 --> 00:45:46,493
- So, it hasn't been long.
- Right.

1180
00:45:46,577 --> 00:45:49,246
- Was she sick?
- No, she wasn't sick.

1181
00:45:49,329 --> 00:45:50,664
It happened in her sleep.

1182
00:45:51,373 --> 00:45:53,333
- Out of nowhere?
- Uh-huh. She was sleeping.

1183
00:45:53,417 --> 00:45:55,586
I got back from work
and turned on the lights…

1184
00:45:56,795 --> 00:45:57,963
and she was sleeping.

1185
00:45:58,046 --> 00:46:00,883
At least at first,
I thought she was just sleeping.

1186
00:46:00,966 --> 00:46:04,136
She was in such
a comfortable position, so I shook her,

1187
00:46:04,219 --> 00:46:05,888
but her body didn't move at all.

1188
00:46:07,014 --> 00:46:09,057
Yes, so, when they arrived,

1189
00:46:09,141 --> 00:46:12,436
they said that it must have been
a heart attack.

1190
00:46:12,519 --> 00:46:14,646
- And so…
- That must've been really shocking.

1191
00:46:17,107 --> 00:46:18,734
My wife had a routine.

1192
00:46:18,817 --> 00:46:21,570
When she got up in the morning,
she would always do the laundry.

1193
00:46:21,653 --> 00:46:26,116
So she must have done the laundry
and laid down in bed at home to rest…

1194
00:46:27,743 --> 00:46:30,204
and passed away while she was doing that.

1195
00:46:30,704 --> 00:46:33,999
The paramedic that responded
to the call told me that, uh…

1196
00:46:35,209 --> 00:46:38,253
quite a bit of time had passed
since she died.

1197
00:46:39,922 --> 00:46:42,800
When I got home,
I found that the laundry was done.

1198
00:46:43,759 --> 00:46:47,221
So when I first saw
that you and Sang-soon had arrived,

1199
00:46:47,304 --> 00:46:48,806
I was so happy.

1200
00:46:54,353 --> 00:46:55,479
Oh, my…

1201
00:46:56,188 --> 00:46:59,316
Because my wife wanted to see you so much,

1202
00:46:59,983 --> 00:47:01,985
looked up to you so much,

1203
00:47:02,069 --> 00:47:05,239
and your married life
with Mr. Lee Sang-soon,

1204
00:47:05,823 --> 00:47:08,242
- she… Yes. She really…
- You guys watched our show?

1205
00:47:09,993 --> 00:47:11,495
…admired it so much.

1206
00:47:12,913 --> 00:47:14,581
So when it comes to dating,

1207
00:47:14,665 --> 00:47:18,085
I met my wife for the first time
in college when I was 20.

1208
00:47:18,669 --> 00:47:20,462
- You met in college?
- College sweethearts.

1209
00:47:20,546 --> 00:47:22,881
- Afterwards--
- His first girlfriend, first love.

1210
00:47:22,965 --> 00:47:24,424
- Your first love?
- First love.

1211
00:47:24,508 --> 00:47:29,721
So we dated for nine years
and got married in 2022.

1212
00:47:29,805 --> 00:47:31,056
Married. Uh-huh.

1213
00:47:31,139 --> 00:47:32,808
That would mean you got to live together

1214
00:47:32,891 --> 00:47:34,768
- for three or four years?
- Yes, yes.

1215
00:47:36,228 --> 00:47:38,730
Sounds like it was
a picture-perfect relationship.

1216
00:47:38,814 --> 00:47:40,232
- That's right.
- From your first love…

1217
00:47:40,315 --> 00:47:42,651
- With her till her final moment.
- …to her final moments.

1218
00:47:42,734 --> 00:47:45,529
It's not easy, that sort of thing.

1219
00:47:45,612 --> 00:47:46,697
You know…

1220
00:47:48,115 --> 00:47:49,950
the thing that bothers me a bit

1221
00:47:50,033 --> 00:47:53,412
is the human tendency
to let go of bad memories.

1222
00:47:54,204 --> 00:47:58,041
It feels like I'm trying to forget
the memories I have of my wife.

1223
00:47:58,125 --> 00:47:59,751
- Against your will.
- Right.

1224
00:47:59,835 --> 00:48:01,503
But I don't want to do that.

1225
00:48:02,838 --> 00:48:03,881
So you know…

1226
00:48:07,092 --> 00:48:08,886
I don't think you'd want to forget.

1227
00:48:08,969 --> 00:48:10,846
- I don't think you'd want that.
- Right.

1228
00:48:10,929 --> 00:48:14,016
But for her memory to fade
even when I don't want it to is just…

1229
00:48:21,315 --> 00:48:22,357
Oh, dear.

1230
00:48:22,983 --> 00:48:24,985
It must be so tough, isn't it?

1231
00:48:56,099 --> 00:49:00,062
The past year must have felt like it just
slipped away for you and your family.

1232
00:49:00,145 --> 00:49:02,356
- Yes, time just…
- It must feel like it vanished

1233
00:49:02,439 --> 00:49:03,649
- into thin air.
- Right.

1234
00:49:04,149 --> 00:49:05,192
I'm still…

1235
00:49:06,360 --> 00:49:09,279
stuck living through the day
before my wife passed away.

1236
00:49:09,363 --> 00:49:10,906
Stuck in time, yeah.

1237
00:49:11,573 --> 00:49:12,824
I just…

1238
00:49:16,244 --> 00:49:20,415
It'd be better if your family
brought her up more, right?

1239
00:49:20,499 --> 00:49:23,251
I'd imagine it must be frustrating
that they don't bring it up

1240
00:49:23,335 --> 00:49:24,795
and avoid talking about it.

1241
00:49:26,254 --> 00:49:30,509
So, I think my family's always walking
on eggshells around me, so…

1242
00:49:30,592 --> 00:49:31,969
I get what you mean.

1243
00:49:32,052 --> 00:49:34,680
Although I don't mean to hurt them…

1244
00:49:37,265 --> 00:49:39,476
It's even more heartbreaking for family.

1245
00:49:41,103 --> 00:49:42,854
My brother was the one
who applied for this.

1246
00:49:42,938 --> 00:49:44,773
Your older brother? To comfort you, huh?

1247
00:49:44,856 --> 00:49:46,650
To have a fun experience.

1248
00:49:46,733 --> 00:49:48,819
Going forward, I feel the need…

1249
00:49:49,987 --> 00:49:51,697
to work towards improving…

1250
00:49:52,781 --> 00:49:55,409
my relationship with my older brother
and my family.

1251
00:49:55,492 --> 00:49:56,743
That's how I feel.

1252
00:49:59,746 --> 00:50:01,999
I think I understand how you feel.

1253
00:50:09,047 --> 00:50:10,215
Oh, boy.

1254
00:50:10,882 --> 00:50:12,134
Okay.

1255
00:50:12,217 --> 00:50:14,428
BREAKFAST PREPARATIONS
ARE COMPLETE IN THE KITCHEN

1256
00:50:16,346 --> 00:50:17,347
Uh, what's…

1257
00:50:29,234 --> 00:50:32,529
CALMLY STARTS SERVING BREAKFAST

1258
00:50:32,612 --> 00:50:34,781
This here is sugar, okay?

1259
00:50:34,865 --> 00:50:36,908
- Oh. Okay. Got it.
- And if you want, some jam.

1260
00:50:39,327 --> 00:50:41,455
- Let's eat. Let's eat.
- Okay.

1261
00:50:41,955 --> 00:50:43,040
- Let's eat.
- Enough crying.

1262
00:50:43,123 --> 00:50:44,124
Yeah.

1263
00:50:46,001 --> 00:50:48,420
PAT

1264
00:50:51,381 --> 00:50:52,841
Why don't you go take a second?

1265
00:51:10,150 --> 00:51:11,735
- Let's go, <i>hyung.</i>
- Mmm.

1266
00:51:12,360 --> 00:51:13,862
They'll come looking for us.

1267
00:51:15,238 --> 00:51:19,284
The reason I couldn't even
bring this up with my family

1268
00:51:19,367 --> 00:51:22,829
is that it would make them
so sad, and they would…

1269
00:51:24,414 --> 00:51:27,084
pity me so much and worry a lot about me.

1270
00:51:27,751 --> 00:51:30,212
Such concerns held me back
from bringing it up,

1271
00:51:31,338 --> 00:51:34,966
but the consolation she provided
felt so genuine,

1272
00:51:35,050 --> 00:51:37,219
so I was really grateful to her for that.

1273
00:51:44,392 --> 00:51:47,479
- Hey, this is like a hotel breakfast.
- It's totally a hotel breakfast.

1274
00:51:47,562 --> 00:51:50,440
- A five-star hotel at that.
- Well done.

1275
00:51:50,524 --> 00:51:52,150
MAKING FRENCH TOAST
AND EGGS IS SECOND NATURE NOW

1276
00:51:52,943 --> 00:51:55,112
HYO-RI'S
SIGNATURE PINE NUT PORRIDGE

1277
00:51:56,154 --> 00:51:58,448
SANG-SOON'S
SIGNATURE FRUIT SALAD

1278
00:51:59,074 --> 00:52:00,909
AND SANG-SOON'S SIGNATURE
COFFEE FOR PURE PERFECTION

1279
00:52:00,992 --> 00:52:02,536
You need some porridge.

1280
00:52:03,286 --> 00:52:05,580
- It's good for your stomach.
- Okay. Thanks.

1281
00:52:05,664 --> 00:52:06,706
Eat up.

1282
00:52:06,790 --> 00:52:08,375
- Enjoy.
- Okay.

1283
00:52:08,458 --> 00:52:10,335
- I've never had this.
- Same.

1284
00:52:10,418 --> 00:52:11,962
I've never tried pine nut porridge.

1285
00:52:12,045 --> 00:52:13,588
- Pine nut porridge is great.
- I love porridge.

1286
00:52:13,672 --> 00:52:15,715
- I'll give it a try.
- It's kind of like soup.

1287
00:52:15,799 --> 00:52:16,925
- Like soup, huh?
- Soup.

1288
00:52:17,425 --> 00:52:20,262
THE COFFEE FACTORY
IS ALSO RUNNING NONSTOP

1289
00:52:20,345 --> 00:52:22,973
Drink up. Coffee's here.

1290
00:52:23,056 --> 00:52:24,266
Your coffee's ready. Coffee.

1291
00:52:24,349 --> 00:52:26,768
- Take some coffee.
- Okay, come and get it.

1292
00:52:31,481 --> 00:52:32,524
Mmm!

1293
00:52:33,859 --> 00:52:35,193
The porridge is good.

1294
00:52:36,278 --> 00:52:38,405
It's delicious.
I've never tasted anything like it.

1295
00:52:38,488 --> 00:52:39,531
Yeah, me too.

1296
00:52:39,614 --> 00:52:41,533
- I heard it's good for you.
- Mm-hmm.

1297
00:52:41,616 --> 00:52:42,826
It tastes healthy.

1298
00:52:42,909 --> 00:52:44,452
LOVE THAT HEALTHY TASTE

1299
00:52:45,036 --> 00:52:46,913
When else would I get this luxury?

1300
00:52:46,997 --> 00:52:48,081
You spilled some.

1301
00:52:51,168 --> 00:52:53,086
TASTY

1302
00:52:53,170 --> 00:52:55,630
Time to eat.

1303
00:52:55,714 --> 00:52:58,383
THE BROTHERS RETURN
AND GRAB A PLATE OF FOOD TOO

1304
00:52:58,466 --> 00:52:59,718
- Do we start down here?
- Yes.

1305
00:52:59,801 --> 00:53:01,303
- What's this?
- If you're gonna eat this,

1306
00:53:01,386 --> 00:53:02,387
use the toaster.

1307
00:53:03,013 --> 00:53:04,472
Are you feeling better?

1308
00:53:04,556 --> 00:53:05,974
- Huh?
- Are you feeling better?

1309
00:53:06,057 --> 00:53:08,143
- I took some medicine. I'm good.
- What is it, sinuses?

1310
00:53:08,226 --> 00:53:10,061
She was feeling under the weather.

1311
00:53:10,145 --> 00:53:11,104
SERIOUS

1312
00:53:12,939 --> 00:53:15,192
- Please don't get sick.
- What? Where were you?

1313
00:53:15,275 --> 00:53:16,776
- I think it might be better if…
- Not really.

1314
00:53:16,860 --> 00:53:19,404
- I was just resting.
- …someone else tells her that. Kwang-soo.

1315
00:53:19,487 --> 00:53:21,865
- I'm fine. Okay.
- Seriously, don't get sick though.

1316
00:53:21,948 --> 00:53:24,868
- Seriously, don't get sick though.
- I won't. I promise.

1317
00:53:24,951 --> 00:53:26,870
Hey, don't get sick.

1318
00:53:26,953 --> 00:53:28,121
- Min-ju.
- Yeah, yeah.

1319
00:53:28,205 --> 00:53:30,582
- Don't get sick.
- Don't get sick or else.

1320
00:53:30,665 --> 00:53:33,126
- Ha-na, don't get sick.
- Okay, thank you.

1321
00:53:33,210 --> 00:53:34,211
We'll be mad if you do.

1322
00:53:34,294 --> 00:53:36,254
- Ha-na, don't get sick.
- Okay. That's really touching.

1323
00:53:36,338 --> 00:53:39,257
If you get sick, I'm gonna go berserk.

1324
00:53:39,341 --> 00:53:40,425
- You hear me?
- Yes.

1325
00:53:40,508 --> 00:53:41,551
- Don't get sick.
- Understood.

1326
00:53:41,635 --> 00:53:43,345
- Don't get sick, I-an.
- Yes, sir.

1327
00:53:43,428 --> 00:53:45,096
- If you do, I'll be furious.
- Okay.

1328
00:53:45,889 --> 00:53:46,973
SUDDENLY EMBARRASSED

1329
00:53:47,057 --> 00:53:48,934
- Don't get sick, Hye-jeong.
- Okay.

1330
00:53:49,017 --> 00:53:50,769
If you get sick, it'll hurt my feelings.

1331
00:53:50,852 --> 00:53:51,853
Really?

1332
00:53:51,937 --> 00:53:52,938
- Hye-jeong!
- Yes?

1333
00:53:53,021 --> 00:53:55,732
- Don't get sick, okay?
- I heard you. Sheesh.

1334
00:53:55,815 --> 00:53:58,610
- Hye-jeong, don't get sick.
- I heard you. I said I heard you.

1335
00:53:58,693 --> 00:54:00,779
- Seriously. Promise me.
- Don't get sick.

1336
00:54:00,862 --> 00:54:02,530
- Okay.
- Look at us, damn it!

1337
00:54:03,406 --> 00:54:04,991
- Look at us when you talk.
- Right.

1338
00:54:05,075 --> 00:54:06,660
Look at us when you talk.

1339
00:54:06,743 --> 00:54:08,453
- Thank you for the meal.
- All right, enjoy.

1340
00:54:08,536 --> 00:54:09,913
- Dig in.
- Okay.

1341
00:54:09,996 --> 00:54:11,373
- Take a seat.
- Eat.

1342
00:54:11,456 --> 00:54:12,582
- Enjoy your meal.
- Eat up.

1343
00:54:12,666 --> 00:54:14,793
- Enjoy, everyone.
- Enjoy your meal.

1344
00:54:14,876 --> 00:54:15,961
- Director?
- Yes?

1345
00:54:16,044 --> 00:54:17,212
Please have some.

1346
00:54:17,295 --> 00:54:18,838
- We should eat.
- Mm-hmm.

1347
00:54:19,881 --> 00:54:21,091
- Is the porridge good?
- Yes.

1348
00:54:21,174 --> 00:54:22,467
It's not bad?

1349
00:54:22,550 --> 00:54:23,718
- I haven't had it yet.
- Eat up.

1350
00:54:23,802 --> 00:54:25,387
- Why aren't you eating?
- I was about to.

1351
00:54:25,470 --> 00:54:27,097
- I haven't gotten around to it.
- Is there more?

1352
00:54:27,180 --> 00:54:28,306
- Hurry up.
- Okay.

1353
00:54:29,349 --> 00:54:32,894
- Seung-hyun, you don't seem to talk much.
- That's right. I don't talk a lot.

1354
00:54:32,978 --> 00:54:34,396
- Did you apply yourself?
- No. Together.

1355
00:54:34,479 --> 00:54:35,480
- Your friend did it?
- Yes.

1356
00:54:35,563 --> 00:54:37,774
- We're co-workers. The three of us.
- You're co-workers?

1357
00:54:37,857 --> 00:54:38,900
- The three of you?
- Yes.

1358
00:54:38,984 --> 00:54:41,111
I didn't tell either of them about it
and just applied.

1359
00:54:41,194 --> 00:54:42,445
Oh, really?

1360
00:54:42,529 --> 00:54:44,739
- What a surprise.
- I was really surprised.

1361
00:54:45,448 --> 00:54:49,411
I notice how the contestants on <i>I'm SOLO</i>
seem to enjoy being on a show like this,

1362
00:54:49,494 --> 00:54:51,621
but what they loved was not having to work

1363
00:54:51,705 --> 00:54:52,998
- while it was going on.
- That's right.

1364
00:54:53,081 --> 00:54:54,624
We usually go into work on weekends too.

1365
00:54:54,708 --> 00:54:55,959
- Even on weekends?
- Yes.

1366
00:54:56,042 --> 00:54:57,794
Wow. What time do you normally get up?

1367
00:54:57,877 --> 00:54:59,963
- Around five o'clock. Yes.
- Five o'clock?

1368
00:55:00,046 --> 00:55:03,383
- You get up so early.
- Yeah, we have to get to work early, so…

1369
00:55:03,466 --> 00:55:04,759
What kind of work is that?

1370
00:55:04,843 --> 00:55:06,344
Our work begins at 6:00 a.m.

1371
00:55:06,428 --> 00:55:07,929
- And ends at 9:00 p.m.
- Hold on.

1372
00:55:08,013 --> 00:55:10,682
- That means you work over 12 hours?
- Let's stop.

1373
00:55:11,891 --> 00:55:14,394
That sounds exhausting.
How do you work for over 12 hours?

1374
00:55:14,477 --> 00:55:16,396
- It is a bit tiring.
- It's very taxing.

1375
00:55:16,479 --> 00:55:20,108
- I thought they were firefighters.
- If they work over 12 hours, they must be.

1376
00:55:20,191 --> 00:55:21,943
So you're firefighters then? Huh?

1377
00:55:22,027 --> 00:55:23,069
- No.
- No.

1378
00:55:24,738 --> 00:55:25,822
So what is it?

1379
00:55:25,905 --> 00:55:27,282
JUST WHO ARE THESE THREE?

1380
00:55:27,365 --> 00:55:28,992
So, about the prizes…

1381
00:55:29,617 --> 00:55:31,077
- That's us.
- Here comes the prize!

1382
00:55:31,161 --> 00:55:33,330
Congratulations
to our first-place winners.

1383
00:55:33,413 --> 00:55:34,706
INDIVIDUAL MATCH 1ST PLACE
YEO-WON

1384
00:55:34,789 --> 00:55:36,333
And for you four…

1385
00:55:36,416 --> 00:55:37,625
Oh, my. Thank you.

1386
00:55:37,709 --> 00:55:39,502
GROUP WINNERS
HYE-JEONG, I-AN, HA-NA, MIN-JU

1387
00:55:39,586 --> 00:55:41,379
- Thank you.
- Congratulations to you all.

1388
00:55:44,883 --> 00:55:47,218
- Hold on. Ha-na. You don't belong there.
- Yes?

1389
00:55:47,302 --> 00:55:48,678
But she did it with us.

1390
00:55:48,762 --> 00:55:49,971
- I did.
- We performed together.

1391
00:55:50,055 --> 00:55:52,140
- But she's on Team Kwang-soo.
- We all sang.

1392
00:55:52,223 --> 00:55:54,017
But if you're on his team, why did you…

1393
00:55:54,976 --> 00:55:57,312
You're right. What the heck?

1394
00:55:57,395 --> 00:55:59,773
I thought it didn't matter in the morning.

1395
00:55:59,856 --> 00:56:01,566
- You just switched teams?
- Are you kidding me?

1396
00:56:01,649 --> 00:56:02,859
Oh, really?

1397
00:56:02,942 --> 00:56:04,652
"We had so much fun."

1398
00:56:04,736 --> 00:56:10,575
<i>We sang in joy</i>
<i>Yodelay, yodelay, yodelayhihi </i>

1399
00:56:10,658 --> 00:56:11,785
THEY SAW IT ALL GO DOWN…

1400
00:56:11,868 --> 00:56:13,411
You're on our side.

1401
00:56:13,953 --> 00:56:15,705
You're joining my team, right?

1402
00:56:17,415 --> 00:56:19,334
- No, I--
- Did you really sing with them?

1403
00:56:19,417 --> 00:56:21,211
I could only see your back.

1404
00:56:22,587 --> 00:56:25,298
- We have to do the dishes.
- Right. I have to do them.

1405
00:56:25,382 --> 00:56:26,966
Oh, I should also help.

1406
00:56:28,009 --> 00:56:30,387
- Should we empty the trash?
- Let me help.

1407
00:56:30,470 --> 00:56:32,263
DONE

1408
00:56:32,347 --> 00:56:34,140
- I'll start washing.
- Mmm.

1409
00:56:34,224 --> 00:56:36,226
- I can rinse.
- Okay.

1410
00:56:36,309 --> 00:56:40,814
So, Woo-seok, um, your work
as an actor really suits you, right?

1411
00:56:41,564 --> 00:56:42,982
- Oh, yeah, suits me so well.
- Right?

1412
00:56:43,066 --> 00:56:44,818
- It's the kind of work I love.
- Right.

1413
00:56:44,901 --> 00:56:46,778
I wish I was a better actor.

1414
00:56:47,779 --> 00:56:48,863
WHAT'S THIS ABOUT ACTING?

1415
00:56:48,947 --> 00:56:52,575
- How come?
- My job requires some acting, that's why.

1416
00:56:52,659 --> 00:56:54,160
- Oh, really?
- It feels like you just

1417
00:56:54,244 --> 00:56:56,663
made a mistake and tried to cover it up.

1418
00:56:57,247 --> 00:57:00,041
He was so surprised by what he said
that his pupils dilated a little.

1419
00:57:00,125 --> 00:57:01,126
Yeah, you slipped up.

1420
00:57:02,252 --> 00:57:05,088
It's nothing, really.
I merely protect the earth for my job.

1421
00:57:05,171 --> 00:57:07,006
I merely protect the earth for my job.

1422
00:57:07,090 --> 00:57:08,216
ACTOR+PROTECTOR OF EARTH?

1423
00:57:08,299 --> 00:57:09,509
Early in the morning, I…

1424
00:57:10,593 --> 00:57:12,846
I go around defeating villains and…

1425
00:57:12,929 --> 00:57:13,930
Huh?

1426
00:57:14,013 --> 00:57:17,559
I go around defeating villains and stuff.
That's why I wake up early.

1427
00:57:17,642 --> 00:57:20,270
- Ah.
- If he gets up early to protect the earth,

1428
00:57:20,353 --> 00:57:23,189
maybe he's a garbage man?
Or something like that?

1429
00:57:23,273 --> 00:57:25,817
- Could it be a cop perhaps?
- Maybe that.

1430
00:57:25,900 --> 00:57:27,819
AN ACTING HERO
WHAT DOES BRYAN DO FOR A LIVING?

1431
00:57:29,779 --> 00:57:32,198
- What's with the laptop?
- I had a question to ask.

1432
00:57:32,282 --> 00:57:33,908
- Show us then.
- It's about this.

1433
00:57:34,742 --> 00:57:36,828
"What kind of attitude
should we have in life

1434
00:57:36,911 --> 00:57:39,873
to keep moving forward
without regret till the end,

1435
00:57:39,956 --> 00:57:41,166
even in the face of fear,

1436
00:57:41,249 --> 00:57:43,918
as we pursue a dream
that seems unattainable?"

1437
00:57:44,002 --> 00:57:46,963
Yes, do something that's not unattainable.

1438
00:57:47,714 --> 00:57:49,132
It only "seems" unattainable.

1439
00:57:49,215 --> 00:57:51,092
I need details, what is it you wanna do?

1440
00:57:51,176 --> 00:57:53,094
I wanna grow my company to the point where

1441
00:57:53,178 --> 00:57:55,388
if my products were
to suddenly disappear one day,

1442
00:57:55,472 --> 00:57:57,515
people wouldn't be able to go
about their daily lives.

1443
00:57:57,599 --> 00:57:58,600
- Oh.
- Ah.

1444
00:57:58,683 --> 00:58:00,977
I think that's the only way
you truly conquer the world.

1445
00:58:01,060 --> 00:58:02,312
You want to conquer the world?

1446
00:58:02,896 --> 00:58:04,439
CONQUER EARTH…?

1447
00:58:04,522 --> 00:58:06,191
That was my dream growing up, yeah.

1448
00:58:06,274 --> 00:58:08,610
Oh, well, that's not so unattainable.

